It is a huge villa complex and not nearly so well known as nearby Pompeii and Herculaneum. Consequently there are few visitors – we had the place virtually to ourselves. The site is impressive. More than 100 rooms have been excavated. They contain a magnificent array of frescoes, many with an architectural theme, and adorned with masks, birds, flowers and fruit. The colours are stunning. Because of its opulence, it is thought that the villa probably belonged to Poppaea Sabina, the second wife of Emperor Nero.
